Title: Ephemeris Refinement For The Esa-Ariel Mission

Summary: The ESA-Ariel mission will characterise the atmospheres of ~1000 exoplanets. To facilitate this survey, it is critical that the ephemerides of these targets are well-known. We propose to ensure that there is 2-minute data for key currently known exoplanets and TESS Planet Candidates. These data will allow for accurate measurements of the transit mid-time and, therefore, of the planet's period. Hence, we will use the requested data to support the Ariel mission by refining the ephemerides of hundreds of targets.
